  "question": "A 3 year old boy is brought to the clinic by his mother who has noticed a\nmass in his neck. On examination; he has a smooth mass located on the\nlateral aspect of his anterior triangle, near to the angle of the mandible.\nOn ultrasound; it has a fluid filled, anechoic, appearance. What is the\nmost likely cause?",
