  "question": "A 25-year-old junior doctor has a chest x-ray performed as part of a routine insurance medical examination. The x-ray shows evidence of rib notching. Auscultation of his chest reveals a systolic murmur which is loudest at the posterior aspect of the fourth intercostal space. What is the most likely diagnosis?",
