  "answer": "C) Anti phospholipid syndrome= following antibodies Lupus anticoagulant Anti-cardiolipin Anti-β2-glycoprotein Antiphospholipid syndrome, is an autoimmune, hypercoagulable state caused by antiphospholipid antibodies. APS provokes blood clots (thrombosis) in both arteries and veins as well as pregnancy-related complications such as miscarriage, stillbirth, preterm delivery, or severe preeclampsia. The diagnostic criteria requires one clinical event, i.e. thrombosis or pregnancy complication, and two positive blood tests spaced at least 3 months apart. These antibodies are: lupus anticoagulant, anti-cardiolipin and anti-β2-glycoprotein. Antiphospholipid syndrome can be primary or secondary. Primary antiphospholipid syndrome occurs in the absence of any other related disease. Secondary antiphospholipid syndrome occurs with other autoimmune diseases, such as systemic lupu",
