  "answer": "C) Renal adenocarcinoma are the most common renal tumours. These will typically affect the renal parenchyma. Transitional cell carcinoma will usually affect urothelial surfaces. Nephroblastoma would be very rare in this age group. Renal adenocarcinoma may produce cannon ball metastasis in the lung which cause haemoptysis, this is not a feature of PKD.",
  "chapter": "Review",
