  "answer": "B) Blood stained nipple discharge should always be investigated. Nipple fluid cytology is generally unhelpful. Discharge of this type of material is most likely to be due to duct ectasia. Green or brown discharge is most common. Blood stained discharge should raise concern of intraductal papilloma or cancer",
