  "answer": "A) Berrys sign= Absence of carotid pulse due to malignant thyromegaly. Papillary thyroid cancers will tend to spread via lymphatics and present with disease that is nearly always confined to the neck. Follicular carcinomas may metastasise haematogenously and the skull may be the presenting site of disease in between 2 and 8% of patients.",
  "chapter": "Review",
