  "answer": "D) A short history of progressive dysphagia in a middle aged man who has a background history of reflux is strongly suggestive of malignancy. Long standing reflux symptoms may be suggestive of a increased risk of developing Barretts oesophagus. Note that not all patients with Barretts transformation alone are symptomatic. In such cases, the tumours are adenocarcinoma.",
  "chapter": "Review",
