  "question": "A 42 year old lady has had an axillary node clearance for breast malignancy. Post operatively she reports weakness of the shoulder. She is unable to push herself forwards from a wall with the right arm and the scapula is pushed out medially from the chest wall. What is the most likely nerve injury?",
