  "answer": "C) A thoracic cord lesion causes spastic paraperesis, hyperrflexia and extensor plantar responses (UMN lesion), incontinence, sensory loss below the lesion and 'sensory' ataxia.These features typically manifest several weeks later, once spinal shock (in which areflexia predominates) has resolved.",
