  "answer": "A) A small lesion such as this is adequately treated by local excision. The British Association of Dermatology guidelines suggest that excision of conventional BCC (<2cm) with margins of 3-5mm have locoregional control rates of 85%. Morphoeic lesions have higher local recurrence rates.",
  "chapter": "Review",
