  "answer": "A) Secretin causes secretion of water and electrolytes\nCholecystokinin causes enzyme secretion\nWhile secretin will typically increase electrolyte and water volume of\nsecretions, the enzyme content in increased by cholecystokinin.\nSomatostatin will decrease the volume of secretions. Aldosterone will\ntend to conserve electrolytes.",
