  "answer": "E) When assessing patients for carotid surgery, it is important to make sure that their symptoms correlate with the significantly stenosed side. This is not the case in this patient. Carotid endarterectomy is performed to prevent stroke secondary to embolisation for carotid plaque. If the artery is occluded, there is no flow and there can therefore be no embolisation. Surgery is thus not indicated for occluded internal carotid arteries.",
