  "question": "A 57-year-old smoker has a history of intermittent claudication of his right calf. His claudication distance is 0.5 mile (~0.8 km). Angiography reveals a 12-cm stenosis in the proximal superficial femoral artery. This has had no effect on his lifestyle, work or social activities. Select the most likely single treatment for this case.",
