  "question": "A 38 year old lady presents with right upper quadrant pain and nausea. She is otherwise well and her only medical therapy is the oral contraceptive pill which she has taken for many years with no ill effects. Her liver function tests are normal. An ultrasound examination demonstrates a hyperechoic well defined lesion in the left lobe of the liver which measures 14 cm in diameter. What is the most probable underlying cause?",
