  "answer": "B) Cavernous haemangioma often presents with vague symptoms and signs. They may grow to considerable size. Liver function tests are usually normal. The lesions are typically well defined and hyperechoic on ultrasound. A causative link between OCP use and haemangiomata has yet to be established, but is possible.",
