  "answer": "A) Data from multiple RCT's are best displayed using Forest plots. Funnel plots may be used to determine the effect of small studies and their overall effect on the data. Violin plots and Box Whisker plots are often used to graphically display non parametric data from single studies and are not generally used to display data from meta analyses.",
  "chapter": "Review",
