  "question": "A 60 year old male is admitted to the emergency room with a fall. He lives with his wife and still works as a restaurant manager. He has a past history of benign prostatic hypertrophy and is currently taking tamsulosin. He is otherwise fit and healthy. On examination, there is right hip tenderness on movement in all directions. A hip x-ray confirms an intertrochanteric fracture. What is the best management option?",
