  "question": "A 41-year-old woman who is six weeks postpartum presents with a\ntender periareolar lump with nipple retraction. What is the likely\ndiagnosis? Single best answer - select one answer only.",
  "options": {
    "A": "Abscess",
    "B": "Cyst",
    "C": "Fibroadenoma",
    "D": "Intraductal papilloma",
    "E": "Malignancy."
  },
  "answer": "A) The most likely diagnosis of a tender lump in this breastfeeding patient is\na postpartum abscess. The nipple retraction is caused by inflammatory\nfibrosis.",
