  "question": "A 54-year-old female presents with a painless fixed lump in the upper\nouter quadrant of the right breast which has been present for the last\nfour weeks. Mammogram has not revealed any abnormality but\nultrasound has shown a 21mm irregular mass. What is the likely\ndiagnosis? Single best answer - select one answer only.",
