  "question": "A 28-year-old female presents with a two week history of discomfort and a lump in the 6 o’clock region adjacent to the nipple-areolar complex. She is a BRCA 2 carrier, has mild asthma and smokes twelve cigarettes a day. What is the likely diagnosis? Single best answer - select one answer only.",
