  "answer": "D) Sentinel node biopsy reduces the number of patients who require a lymph node dissection, thereby reducing complications such as lymphoedema. However, there is still a false negative result and as such patients should be counseled accordingly. It involves identifying the first nodes which drain the primary tumour and is usually 1-2 nodes but can be more. A combination of radioactive colloid and blue dye (patent blue) can be used but the blue dye is contraindicated in pregnancy.",
