  "question": "A 45-year-old man undergoes an endoscopic retrograde cholangiopancreatography (ERCP) for removal of a common bile duct stone. The procedure is particularly difficult but is eventually successful. Following the operation, he deteriorates badly, developing a pyrexia and severe abdominal pain, with increased amylase of 500. Select the single most likely diagnosis from the options listed below.",
