  "id": 205904,
  "question": "A 76 year old man complains of symptoms of claudication. The decision is made to measure his ankle brachial pressure index. The signal from the dorsalis pedis artery is auscultated with a hand held doppler device. This vessel is the continuation of which of the following?",
  "options": {
    "A": "Posterior tibial artery",
    "B": "Anterior tibial artery",
    "C": "Peroneal artery",
    "D": "Popliteal artery",
    "E": "None of the above"
  },
