  "question": "A 78 year old lady is admitted with a 3 hour history of passage of dark red blood per rectum. Prior to this event, she was otherwise well with no major medical co-morbidities. On examination, she has a mild tachycardia but other vital signs are normal, abdomen is soft and non tender. Digital rectal exam reveals dark blood but no other findings. What is the most likely underlying cause?",
