  "answer": "D) Haematoceles develop over minutes/ hours and occur after the event\n\nThis is a secondary hydrocele which occurs in patients aged 20-40 years. It develops over days/ weeks and there may not be a tense swelling. The underlying testis is NOT palpated therefore indicating a hydrocele. Causes include trauma, infection and tumour.",
