  "answer": "D) Leakage from perivascular lymphatic vessels can lead to significant collections of lymph between the lower pole of the transplanted kidney and the bladder. A lymphocele can present as pain, swelling and impaired renal function within the first year following transplantation. Treatment is by drainage. Percutaneous drainage has a high infection risk and is rarely successful, due to a high recurrence rate. Laparoscopic drainage of the collection in to the abdominal cavity is the treatment of choice.",
  "chapter": "Review",
