  "answer": "E) Post-operative haematomas are common post-splenectomy. They may collect in the subphrenic space, and infection can readily lead to a subphrenic abscess. They may cause an associated pleural effusion as in this case. Characteristically they present with swinging pyrexia, sweats, rigors and left-sided pain on deep inspiration. Treatment is usually by percutaneous drainage. Some operations have a good list of specific complications that are beloved of examiners. Favoured are probably thyroidectomy, splenectomy, laparoscopic cholecystectomy and inguinal hernia repair.",
