  "answer": "B) The saphenous nerve enters the adductor canal but leaves the canal without passing through the adductor hiatus. The saphenous nerve courses with the great saphenous vein and innervates skin of the medial side of the leg and foot. The nerve may be injured during surgical removal of the great saphenous vein, or it may be lacerated as it pierces the wall of the adductor canal.",
