  "question": "A 24-year-old gentleman presents to The Emergency Department with a history of head injury while playing rugby. He was involved with a ‘clash of heads’ with another player during a ‘ruck’. He remembers the events surrounding the event well, and has no amnesia. Collateral history from his friends confirms that there was no loss of consciousness. On examination he is fully orientated, GCS is 15 and all other observations are normal. There is no evidence of focal neurological deficit. Select the most appropriate plan of management for this case.",
