  "answer": "C) 6 weeks. As a general rule, upper limb fractures in adults take 6–8 weeks to heal, while lower limb fractures take 12–16 weeks. These numbers are halved in children. Healing times are affected by fracture type and site, quality of local blood supply, amount of soft tissue interposition and amount of movement at the site of injury. Patient factors, such as anaemia, chronic illness and steroid use, will also have a bearing on healing.",
