  "question": "A 3-year-old boy is brought to the GP practice by his mother. He has been complaining intermittently about abdominal pain. His mother feels that his abdomen is distended. On examination, there is a large mass on the left side of the abdomen which does not cross the midline.\nWhat is the most likely diagnosis?",
