  "question": "A 26-year-old man is admitted with a painful right shoulder following a high speed RTA. Plain radiographs reveal a fractured scapula. He appears systemically well but undergoes a full body CT scan as the casualty registrar quite correctly recognises that this fracture carries a high risk of concomitant soft tissue injury. In which of the following bones does a fracture indicate high energy trauma which could be associated with hidden severe injuries?",
