  "question": "A 45-year-old jockey falls off his horse and sustains a fracture of his distal tibia involving the ankle joint. After initial resuscitation, a senior orthopaedic review determines that stability will be best achieved by external fi xation with a quadrilateral frame. This involves a pin placed in the proximal tibia, linked by rods to another pin which is placed through the calcaneum. The distal pin is inserted from the medial aspect of the calcaneum, about an inch (2.5 cm) superior and towards the toes, away from the heel. Which local nerve is most likely to be damaged by improper pin placement?",
