  "question": "A 47-year-old alcoholic presents to the Emergency Department with central abdominal pain and vomiting. She prefers to sit up as the pain aggravates on lying supine and on eating. On examination, her pulse rate is 140/min, her temperature is 38.2°C, and there is periumbilical discoloration. What is the most likely diagnosis?",
