  "question": "Intra cranial pressure is governed by the principles of the Monroe-Kellie\ndoctrine. To which of the following does this concept not apply?",
  "options": {
    "A": "A 2 month old child",
    "B": "A 2 year old child",
    "C": "A 5 year old child",
    "D": "A 10 year old child",
    "E": "An adult"
  },
  "answer": "A) The Monroe-Kelly Doctrine assumes that the cranial cavity is a rigid box.\nIn children with non fused fontanells this is not the case.",
