  "question": "A 45-year-old woman has recently been diagnosed with a palpable node positive breast cancer initially treated by a wide local excision and axillary clearance. Her tumour is 26 mm, grade 3 with 3/19 nodes positive. Her pre chemotherapy staging scans (CT and bone scan) show indeterminate lung nodules. She is enquiring about her prognosis and rationale for adjuvant therapy. What is her NPI (Nottingham prognostic index)? Select one answer only.",
