  "answer": "D) The Nottingham prognostic index gives a numerical score to individual breast cancers and can act as a guide for the need for chemotherapy and give patients prognostic information which they can understand. It divides cancers into 5 prognostic groups. It is calculated from size in cm (x 0.2) + grade (13) + number of involved lymph nodes (0=1, 1-3=2, >3=3).",
