  "answer": "A) The external oblique will be encountered first in this location. The rectus sheath lies more medially.\nThe external oblique muscle is the most superficial of the abdominal wall muscles. It originates from the 5th to 12th ribs and passes inferomedially to insert into the linea alba, pubic tubercle and anterior half of the iliac crest. It is innervated by the thoracoabdominal nerves (T7-T11) and sub costal nerves.",
