  "answer": "A) The portal vein transports 70% of the blood supply to the liver, while the hepatic artery provides 30%. The portal vein contains the products of digestion. The arterial and venous blood is dispersed by sinusoids to the central veins of the liver lobules; these drain into the hepatic veins and then into the IVC. The caudate lobe drains directly into the IVC rather than into other hepatic veins.",
