  "question": "An 83 year old woman is admitted with a left intertrochanteric neck of femur fracture. On examination, the patient is found to have an ejection systolic murmur loudest in the aortic region. There is no radiation of the murmur to the carotid arteries. Her ECG is normal. What is the most likely lesion?",
