  "question": "A 75 year old man is admitted with sudden onset severe generalised abdominal pain, vomiting and a single episode of bloody diarrhoea. On examination, he looks unwell and is in uncontrolled atrial fibrillation. Although diffusely tender his abdomen is soft. What is the most likely diagnosis?",
