  "question": "A 14 year old female is admitted with sudden onset right iliac fossa pain. She is otherwise well and on examination has some right iliac fossa tenderness but no guarding. She is afebrile. Urinary dipstick is normal. Her previous menstrual period two weeks ago was normal and pregnancy test is negative. What is the most likely underlying diagnosis?",
